						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Achyutayyadēva-Mahārāya Year: Śaka 1454: 1532 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged at the end and letters are not neatly engraved. Seems to assign some (shepherds) Ulakītti, son of Maṇampoṉṉikōṉ of Koṉṉandaparambil, Tirumalai, and Paramaṉ as <hi rend="italic">tiruviḷakkukuḍi</hi> to supply six <hi rend="italic">(kuṟuṇi ?)</hi> of ghee by the measure <hi rend="italic">sūlakkāl</hi> annually to the god Tirumalar-uḍaiyanayiṉār at Dēvakkapuram, for the merit of the king. </p>						

						</summary>
